Alabama eliminated its at-large seats, going from 6 districts and 2 at-large seats to 8 districts.  The state also elected a full delegation of Democrats, voting out the two Republicans.

title: 1876–77 United States House of Representatives elections
added: <!--{{Main|1876 United States House of Representatives elections in Connecticut}}-->
{{See also|List of United States Representatives from Connecticut|1876 United States Senate special election in Connecticut}}

Connecticut had been electing is members late in the cycle, even after the terms had begun.  But starting in 1876, the state joined the others in electing its members on the November 7, 1876 [[Election Day (United States)|Election Day]]. The delegation remained 3 Democrats and 1 Republican.
